    "description": "<h4>BAIT</h4><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Bait is found only via <strong>camp activities</strong> or specific <strong>merchants</strong>.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Merchants who sell bait are rare, limited only to spots where fishing should be common and expected. It is up to the GM to discern if a bait-selling merchant is appropriate for the location.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Bait is designed to be <strong>limited</strong>, with a recommendation for each player only being able to buy up to <strong>10 units of bait per session</strong>. An example Zenit conversion is at least 20 Zenit for 1 simple bait.</span></p><p></p><h4>CAMP ACTIVITIES</h4><p>With the addition of the <strong>Angler</strong> class comes a special <strong>Camp Activity</strong> available for <strong>resting scenes</strong>.</p><h5></h5><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>CAMP ACTIVITY</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>TARGET</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-skills.Item.dSAgznaLIU5x29GT]{Bait Finding}</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>A character with the Angler class</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><p>You spend your time looking for bait in the area; describe how and roll <strong>1d6</strong>. (@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-rollable-tables.RollTable.EdwaC4A1eZVFUYNW]{Bait Finding})</p><ul><li><p><strong>1. None, really</strong>? You do not manage to find bait, and you wear yourself out so that you do not recover Hit Points and Mind Points during this rest.</p></li><li><p><strong>2. It's Something, I guess...</strong> You find 1 Simple Bait.</p></li><li><p><strong>3-5. A respectable find!</strong> You find 3 Simple Bait.</p></li><li><p><strong>6. No way!</strong> You find 1 Unique Bait.</p></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h4>FISHING</h4><p>Fishing works by making use of a <strong>fishing dice</strong>: it determine if you would be able to catch a fish in that particular area. The GM determines the fishing die based on how <strong>feasible</strong> it would be to catch a fish in that spot.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>FEASABILITY OF FISHING</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>FISHING DICE</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fishes are guaranteed to bite</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\">d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>It's easy to catch fishes here</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\">d8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fishes may or may not be caught here</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\">d10 (Default)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>It's hard, but not impossible to catch fishes here</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\">d12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>There is little to no chance of catching a fish</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\">d20</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p>Roll your <strong>fishing die</strong> and refer to this table (@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-rollable-tables.RollTable.BsRVNqECIlz6OhsE]{Fishing})</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>ROLL</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CATCH OF THE DAY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ADDITIONAL NOTES</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>1</strong></p></td><td><p>Discovery Fish</p></td><td><p><em>Refer to discovery fish section.</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2 - 5</strong></p></td><td><p>Weaponry Fish</p></td><td><p><em>Refer to weaponry fish section.</em></p><p><em>If using <strong>Unique</strong> bait, the player choose the <strong>attributes </strong>and the GM may add a <strong>quality</strong> to the fish.</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>6</strong></p></td><td><p>Item Fish / Zenit</p></td><td><p><em>Refer to item fish / zenit reward section.</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>7+</strong></p></td><td><p>No Fish</p></td><td><p><em>Bait is lost. (Unless you have <strong>Improved Fishing</strong>).</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>MAX</strong></p></td><td><p>Bad Times</p></td><td><p><em><strong>Optional Rule:</strong> Something bad happens to the party!</em></p><p><em>Note that <strong>Bad Times</strong> only happens on a <strong>d12</strong> and above.</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h4>OPTIONAL RULE: BAD TIMES</h4><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">There can be times where fishing leads to minor or major <strong>disasters</strong>. This is where the Bad Times optional rule comes to play.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">On rolling the max value on a <strong>fishing die</strong> starting on a <strong>d12</strong>, the GM may opt to choose a <strong>Danger</strong> that appropriately fits the scenario. Characters should generally be able to overcome a danger through a series of <strong>Checks</strong> or a <strong>Conflict</strong> scene.</span></p><ul><li><p>The risk of losing an important item.</p></li><li><p>A dangerous fish inflicting Status Effects.</p></li><li><p>A fish has decided to fight back.</p></li><li><p>A tiny fish hell bent on ruining your day.</p></li><li><p>Trash and litter that you would need to sort.</p></li></ul><p>It is unlikely for the characters to be directly damaged by Bad Times, but in the case where this happens, refer to the damage table provided in the <strong>Dangers</strong> section of the <strong>Core Rulebook</strong> (page <strong>108</strong>).</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Level</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Minor Damage</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Heavy Damage</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Massive Damage</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>5+</strong></p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>20+</strong></p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>40+</strong></p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>80</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h4>ORIGIN TO DAMAGE TYPE CONVERSION</h4><p>If the Origin does not apply to any of the following, the damage type is <strong>Physical</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>ORIGIN</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>DAMAGE TYPE</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ORIGIN</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>DAMAGE TYPE</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Ardent</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Fire</em></p></td><td><p><strong>Spiritual</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Light</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Corrupted</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Dark</em></p></td><td><p><strong>Terrestrial</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Earth</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Glacial</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Ice</em></p></td><td><p><strong>Aquatic</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Poison</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Mechanical</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Bolt</em></p></td><td><p><strong>Aerial</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Wind</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h4>WEAPONRY FISH</h4><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Fish can be used by the Angler as deadly weapons for combat.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Note that an Angler can still use these fish <strong>even if they normally lack the ability</strong> to handle martial weapons, and all weaponry fish are <strong>one-handed unless stated otherwise</strong>. The damage type of the fish then depends on the <strong>origin</strong> of the fish (see Origin to Damage Type Conversion table).</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Roll <strong>4d12</strong> and refer to this table. (@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-rollable-tables.RollTable.SAqF8VAl82gd4sbA]{Weaponry Fish})<br />If you are not using any bait, halve the result of the 3rd and 4th d12s. (@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-rollable-tables.RollTable.fWpbhmKeSHJjffT3]{Weaponry Fish (No Bait)})</span></p><table><tbody><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p><strong>ROLL</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ATTR 1</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ATTR 2</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CATEGORY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>DAMAGE</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>1</p></td><td><p>DEX</p></td><td><p>DEX</p></td><td><p>Thrown</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 4 + SL】</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>2</p></td><td><p>DEX</p></td><td><p>DEX</p></td><td><p>Bow</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 4 + SL】</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>3</p></td><td><p>DEX</p></td><td><p>DEX</p></td><td><p>Heavy</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 6 + SL】</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>4</p></td><td><p>INS</p></td><td><p>INS</p></td><td><p>Flail</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 6 + SL】</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>5</p></td><td><p>INS</p></td><td><p>INS</p></td><td><p>Dagger</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 8 + SL】<br /></strong>Two-Handed</p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>6</p></td><td><p>INS</p></td><td><p>INS</p></td><td><p>Brawling</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 8 + SL】<br /></strong>Two-Handed</p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>7</p></td><td><p>WLP</p></td><td><p>WLP</p></td><td><p>Arcane</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 10 + SL】</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>8</p></td><td><p>WLP</p></td><td><p>WLP</p></td><td><p>Firearm <strong>@ICON[martial]</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 10 + SL】</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>9</p></td><td><p>WLP</p></td><td><p>WLP</p></td><td><p>Heavy <strong>@ICON[martial]</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 12 + SL】<br /></strong>Two-Handed</p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>10</p></td><td><p>MIG</p></td><td><p>MIG</p></td><td><p>Spear <strong>@ICON[martial]</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 12 + SL】<br /></strong>Two-Handed</p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>11</p></td><td><p>MIG</p></td><td><p>MIG</p></td><td><p>Sword <strong>@ICON[martial]</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 14 + SL】<br /></strong>Two-Handed</p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"127\"><p>12</p></td><td><p>MIG</p></td><td><p>MIG</p></td><td><p>Your Choice</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>【HR + 14 + SL】<br /></strong>Two-Handed</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h5>WEAPONRY FISH EXAMPLES</h5><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>NAME</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ACCURACY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CATEGORY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>DAMAGE</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>QUALITY</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Jellyfish</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【DEX + DEX】</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Flail</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【HR + 8 + SL】bolt</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Two-handed ⬩ Melee ⬩ No Quality</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>NAME</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ACCURACY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CATEGORY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>DAMAGE</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>QUALITY</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Hammerhead @ICON[martial]</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【MIG + MIG】</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Heavy</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【HR + 10 + SL】 physical</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">One-handed ⬩ Melee ⬩ No Quality</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>NAME</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ACCURACY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CATEGORY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>DAMAGE</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>QUALITY</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Lava Archerfish @ICON[martial]</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【DEX + INS】</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Firearm</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【HR + 12 + SL】 fire</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Two-handed ⬩ Ranged ⬩ Attacks with this fish target Magic Defense</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>NAME</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ACCURACY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CATEGORY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>DAMAGE</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>QUALITY</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Swampfish</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【WLP + WLP】</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Arcane</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【HR + 4 + SL】poison</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">One-handed ⬩ Melee ⬩ No Quality</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>NAME</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>ACCURACY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CATEGORY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>DAMAGE</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>QUALITY</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Swordfish</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【DEX + MIG】</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>Sword</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><strong>【HR + 6 + SL】 physical</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">One-handed ⬩ Melee ⬩ No Quality</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h4>ITEM FISH / ZENIT REWARD</h4><p>There are instances where the fish caught by the Angler is not fit for combat, but works well as <strong>components</strong> for other things such as <strong>delicacies</strong> and <strong>projects</strong>. These fish would have <strong>qualities based on their origins</strong> designed by the GM.</p><p>Check the <strong>Winter Holiday Bonus 2022: Forging Rules</strong> to see example of potential qualities based on origin.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>BAIT</strong></p></td><td data-colwidth=\"213\"><p><strong>REWARD</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>OTHER</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>No Bait</strong></p></td><td data-colwidth=\"213\"><p>Zenit amount</p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><em>Zenit worth should not go past 500z</em></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Simple Bait</strong></p></td><td data-colwidth=\"213\"><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Item fish with a max Zenit worth of 1000z</span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><em>Item fish would count as an <strong>ingredient</strong> (taste would be randomized based on the gourmet table) as well as have <strong>qualities</strong> based on its origin to work as a <strong>crafting component.</strong></em></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Unique Bait</strong></p></td><td data-colwidth=\"213\"><p><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\">Item fish with a max Zenit worth of 2000z</span></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>^</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><h4>DISCOVERY FISH</h4><p>During the course of your fishing journey, there are chances for the character to reel in <strong>special</strong> fishes called Discovery Fish.</p><p>Discovery Fishes are by design an uncommon occurrence, so the GM should make sure each and every one of them is useful (as well as interesting!). Feel free to make Discovery Fish <strong>better between bait tiers</strong>: a Discovery found without using bait should <strong>not</strong> be as good as Discovery found with <strong>Unique</strong>-rank bait.</p><p></p><h4>DISCOVERY FISH EXAMPLES</h4><p><strong>NO BAIT</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td data-colwidth=\"123\"><p><strong>Bomb Fish</strong></p></td><td><p><em>Deal <strong>minor damage</strong> to all enemies.</em></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"123\"><p><strong>Healing Fish</strong></p></td><td><p><em>Heals an ally for 30 Hit Points.</em></p></td></tr><tr><td data-colwidth=\"123\"><p><strong>Status Fish</strong></p></td><td><p><em>Cure an ally of one <strong>Status effect</strong>.</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p><strong>SIMPLE BAIT</strong></p><div class=\"tableWrapper\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;overflow-x:auto\"><table style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:641px;border-collapse:collapse;background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary);margin:0.5em 0px;table-layout:fixed;overflow:hidden;min-width:148px\"><colgroup style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><col style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;width:123px\"></col><col style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"></col></colgroup><tbody style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;border-width:1px;border-style:solid;border-color:rgb(226, 232, 240) black;border-image:initial;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;position:relative\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px;font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-size:16px;line-height:1.45em\"><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif\"><strong>Domination Fish</strong></span></p></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;border-width:1px;border-style:solid;border-color:rgb(226, 232, 240) black;border-image:initial;padding:0.25em 0px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;position:relative\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px;font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-size:16px;line-height:1.45em\"><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><em>Choose a target. For their next turn, they have to choose their ally as their target for attacks and spells.</em></span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;border-width:1px;border-style:solid;border-color:rgb(226, 232, 240) black;border-image:initial;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;position:relative\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px;font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-size:16px;line-height:1.45em\"><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif\"><strong>Shield Fish</strong></span></p></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;border-width:1px;border-style:solid;border-color:rgb(226, 232, 240) black;border-image:initial;padding:0.25em 0px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;position:relative\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px;font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-size:16px;line-height:1.45em\"><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><em>Choose a target. Until the start of your next turn, your ally is <strong>covered under guard rules</strong> and <strong>cannot be targeted</strong>.</em></span></p></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;border-width:1px;border-style:solid;border-color:rgb(226, 232, 240) black;border-image:initial;padding:0.25em 0px 0.25em 2px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;position:relative\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px;font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-size:16px;line-height:1.45em\"><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif\"><strong>Type Fish</strong></span></p></td><td style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;border-width:1px;border-style:solid;border-color:rgb(226, 232, 240) black;border-image:initial;padding:0.25em 0px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;position:relative\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px;font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-size:16px;line-height:1.45em\"><span style=\"font-family:'PT Sans Narrow',sans-serif\"><em>Until the start of your next turn, all of your ally attacks become a specific <strong>type</strong>. </em></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0px;font-family:'PT Sans Narrow', sans-serif;font-style:normal;fo